div1.p: In the District Court of the third Judical District of Washington Teritory holding at Seattle King County:-
In the matter of the application of Leonard Martin for Habeas Corpus writ and order etc against } JWGeorge US Marshal and John HMCGrand Sheriff-} 4432 Order NO 4432

This cause comming on to be heard before me upon the application of Leonard Martin for an order of discharge upon a writ of Habeas Corpus on the said applicant alleging that he was illegallu restrained of his liberty by the above named respondednts JWGeorge and John H MCGraw, and after hearing the application argued etc, both partices being represented by attorneys, - and after hearing the same, and the Court being fullly advised, grants said order of application discharging the said Leonard Martin is appearing to the Court that the said
Leonard Martin is illegally restrained of his liberty by the said J.W. George amd JHMcGraw and it is further ordered that the cost of this procedding including the sum of ten ($10) dollars attorneys fee for applicants attorney and other costs and disbursments of this action be entered against the said JW. George and John H McGraw, and the execution issue therefor against the property of said respondents JWGeorge and JHMcGraw
In the WT Dist Ct for 3rd judicial Dist of Washi Territory at Yeaute King Co 4432
In the matter of Leonard MArtin application for Habeas Corpus
Order granting discharge and judgmente for
FILED JUN 1 1885 James Seavey, Clerk. By James P Ludlow Deputy Clerk.
